$interpreted: Dylan: This is too much! You're the general and you let the Queen run off to Maple Lake without reporting it!?
Jerome: I didn't believe the Queen would send you as a messenger, so I had to find all this out by myself. General, this time your unruliness has gone too far!
Fredrica: Do you all have to be so mean? I'll take you to go see the Queen...
Angelia: Gen...General Levon! What are you doing here?
Dylan: Queen Angelia! You...
Puggi: My...my successor.
Puggi: I...I've done my best...the player's reward...I give to you...take my place...as its protector.
Sione: General Levon, put that thing down!
Dylan: I think some paper is coming out...what on earth is this thing?
Jerome: Looks like...a portrait?
Angelia: ...Naya, what are we going to do? I hear something in my mind...it's telling me to command everyone to attack General Levon.
Angelia: Have I...changed again? Am I doing the right thing?
Naya: Angelia, not at all. Your decision is the right one. Everyone is thinking what you're thinking.
Angelia: If that's the way it is...
Angelia: Troops...attack! Do not let them see those photos!
Sione: General Levon, that's an offense!
Sharice: Brutish men, I demand you turn your eyes away!
Dylan: What in Vendacti's name is this!?
Jerome: Why do they want to attack us...General Lucien, help!
Fredrica: I. don't. want. to. This "unruly" woman wants to continue to be unruly.
Naya: Success~
Dylan: What the hell are you all doing!!!??
Angelia: Sorry. That attack was a necessary evil that had to be done against my will.
Dylan: We'll discuss that later. As Queen, you snuck out of the Kingdom of the Sun.
Dylan: If something happened, do you know how serious the effects would be?
Sione: Sorry, we convinced the Queen to come out and get distracted.
Naya: That's right. If you want to cast the blame, you ought to punish us.
Angelia: Naya, Sione, don't say anymore. It was my own idea to come, so I am willing to take on all responsibility.
Dylan: That stressful expression of yours has eased up quite a bit. Looks like this vacation has been good for you.
Angelia: General Levon?
Dylan: But next time you feel pressure, I hope you can come to me to talk it over.
Dylan: After all, the late King William did give me this responsibility. You're as important to me as a daughter would be.
Angelia: Oh...I know. I'm really sorry about sneaking out like that.
Dylan: Well, the vacation is just about wrapping up. We'll wait here for all of you. Why don't you get your luggage together and we'll head home together?
Hestia: Yan-Bo, did Sharice and them all leave?
Yan-Bo: Yes. Say good-bye to you, they would've liked. Find you, they could not. Anxious to leave, they were. Left immediately, they did.
Hestia: Oh. Well, what about their stuff? Platypus found this at the bottom of the lake.
Yan-Bo: Let me take care of that. Next time they come I'll give it to them.
Hestia: They're going to come back? Great!

Yan-Bo: Of course. Two roads diverged in a wood, and I,
I took the one less traveled by,
And that has made all the difference~
Puggi: ...Bickering Baboons! I won't give up. I've got to steal it back!
Puggi: I've also got to get one of those swimming outfits. I'll give it to Pang to wear. That'll at least satisfy some of the players...
Puggi: Ooh-wah!
Puggi: A letter? Let me see...
Puggi: "Tonight, I, Thief of the Gleaming Star, will steal the legendary delicacy desired by the Desert Lizards that is temporarily being stored at Maple Lake. Kindly await the delivery."
Puggi: We don't have anything like that here. Stupid idiot sent the letter to the wrong address...
Puggi: Hey, isn't that me?
Puggi: Wahh!!! Spare my life, I'm sure we can work something out!!
